data.description: Magnificent Opportunity! They Aren't Making Any More Guadalupe River Frontage. Savor In Peace-Tranquility & Fun. Truly Enjoy Life On This Quaint 1933 +/- Square Foot Home On The Guadalupe River. Located Upriver From  Tubers, This Charming Single Story Offers Three Bedrooms, Two Full Bathrooms And A Study, Which Could Also Be Used As An Additional Bedroom. Easy Backyard River Access Leads To A Cute Island In The Water Perfect For Fishing, Kayaking/Canoeing, Or Taking In Some Sunshine. Incredible Pecan, Cypress & Fruit Trees. A Spacious Shed Allows For Storing Floats, Fishing Tools, Or Other Water Toys. Also, Could Be Used As A Workshop/Hobbyshop. Close To Boat Ramps, Numerous Restaurants, And Brookshire Brothers, This Convenient Location Makes This Waterfront Property A Dream Come True!
